Defendant Kali Marie Doyle in court with attorney Joshua Davis Uller.  Defendant Kali Marie Doyle in custody.  Denis John Stingl appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 10 YEARS, with credit for 203 days time served; the INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 5 YEARS; the MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION is 5 YEARS.  The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and is eligible for the "Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program".
Defendant shall provide a DNA sample for the Data Bank and pay all appropriate costs by 9.21.15 or a civil judgment is ordered (civil judgment can be taken from prison wages).
Court ordered defendant to pay all applicable court costs and surcharges by 9.21.15 or a civil judgment is ordered (civil judgment can be taken from prison wages).
Court advised defendant that as a convicted felon he may never possess a firearm or body armor. Court advised defendant that her voting rights are suspended and she may not vote in any election until her civil rights are restored. 
